    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Followers of mysticism, such as beliefs in the existence of important realities beyond perceptual or intellectual understanding that are accessible by subjective experience, such as by intuition or meditation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>神祕主義的追隨者，相信超越感知或人類知識理解的存在的，並透過直覺或冥想等主觀經驗獲得接觸。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Anhänger von Mystizismen, wie dem Glauben an die Existenz von bedeutenden Realitäten, die über Wahrnehmung oder Intellektuelles Verstehen hinausgehen und durch subjektive Erfahrungen wie Intuition oder Meditation zugänglich sind.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
